Class TextMiddleNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.application.components.TEITextStruct.TextMiddleNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TextMiddleNode
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is for registering a single TextNode and text shown after the label and before the next label.

    Miguel Urízar Salinas
    See Also:

      • AddLabel

        public int AddLabel(java.lang.String name,
           java.lang.String value,
           int parent,
           int identifier,
           java.lang.String afterText)
        Inserts a new node in this node or any of the child nodes.

        Only useful for new nodes, not modifying them.

        Parameters:
        name - Name of the label of the new node
        value - Text to insert in the new node
        parent - Parent to contain the new node
        identifier - Number that identifies the new node
        afterText - Text to insert after the new node in the parent
        Returns:
        0 if node is correctly inserted or -1 if there was a problem inserting it

      • CreateLabel

        public int CreateLabel(int parentId,
              java.lang.String newLabelName,
              int beginTextId,
              int beginTextOffset,
              int endTextId,
              int endTextOffset,
              int newLabelId)
        Creates a new label with the selected text offsets defined, it changes automatically child nodes.
        Parameters:
        parentId - Identification number for the parent Label where the child node will be created
        newLabelName - Name of the new label to be generated.
        beginTextId - Id of the label related to the afterText where the new label starts. -1 implies that the new label starts in the innerText of the parent node.
        beginTextOffset - Offset where the text starts.
        endTextId - Id of the label related to the afterText where the new label ends. -1 implies that the new label ends in the innerText of the parent node.
        endTextOffset - Offset where the text ends.
